  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
    <title> DIP_FINGER_SWELLING_Orthopedic_case_sheet_part</title>
    <link id="light-styles" rel="stylesheet" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
    <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
    <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
  </head>
  <body> <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode"> Dark Mode</button>
    <div class="General">
      <h3>1ST COMPLAINT: SWELLING OF FINGER-TIP JOINTS (DIP Joints)</h3>
      <!-- S: Site -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site
          &amp; Distribution</span> <span class="verbal">"Which fingers are
          affected? Is it on one hand or both?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Which joints? Just the end joints (DIPs), or the middle (PIPs) and
            knuckle (MCPs) joints too?</li>
          <li class="rheumatic">Symmetrical (same joints on both hands) vs.
            Asymmetrical?</li>
          <li class="rheumatic">Are any other joints in your body affected
            (e.g., toes, knees, back)?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- O: Onset -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <span class="verbal">"When did you first notice the swelling? Did it
          come on suddenly or gradually over many years?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>ACUTE (overnight): <span class="rheumatic">Gout</span>, <span class="infectious emergency">Septic
              Arthritis</span></li>
          <li>GRADUAL (over months/years): <b class="ortho-specific">Classic
              for Osteoarthritis</b></li>
          <li>SUBACUTE (over weeks/months): <b class="rheumatic">Psoriatic
              Arthritis, Rheumatoid Arthritis</b></li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- D: Duration -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <span class="verbal">"How long has this been a problem for you?"</span>
      </li>
      <!-- A/R: Aggravating / Relieving Factors -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>:
          Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span> <span class="verbal">"Is
          there anything that makes the pain or stiffness better or worse?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>AGGRAVATING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Use,</li>
            <li>&nbsp;gripping, </li>
            <li>cold weather (Osteoarthritis).</li>
          </ul>
          <li>RELIEVING: </li>
          <ul>
            <li>Rest (Osteoarthritis), </li>
            <li>Movement (Inflammatory), </li>
            <li>NSAIDs (Inflammatory).</li>
          </ul>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- C: Character (THE KEY DIFFERENTIATOR) -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>:
          Character</span> <span class="verbal">"Can you describe the swelling?
          Does it feel hard and bony, or more soft and puffy? Is there much
          stiffness?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>SWELLING TYPE:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="ortho-specific"><b>Hard, Bony Swelling (Heberden's
                  Nodes) -&gt; <b class="ortho-specific">Osteoarthritis (OA)</b></b></li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Soft, Boggy, "Sausage-like" Swelling
                (Dactylitis) -&gt; <b class="rheumatic">Psoriatic Arthritis
                  (PsA)</b></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>STIFFNESS (Crucial Differentiator):</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="rheumatic"><b>Morning Stiffness &gt; 30 minutes? -&gt;
                  <b class="rheumatic">Inflammatory Arthritis (PsA, RA)</b></b></li>
              <li class="ortho-specific">Stiffness is brief (&lt; 30 mins) or
                occurs after rest ("gelling") -&gt; <b class="ortho-specific">Osteoarthritis</b></li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>ASSOCIATED PAIN:</b> Is it a deep ache or is it red, hot, and
            intensely painful?</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Radiation -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>:
          Radiation</span> <span class="verbal">"Does the pain travel or
          radiate anywhere from the joints?"</span> </li>
      <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>:
          Associated Symptoms</span> <span class="verbal">"Have you noticed any
          other symptoms at all, for example any changes to your skin or nails?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li class=" derma rheumatic"><b>SKIN &amp; NAIL CHANGES
              (Key for Psoriatic Arthritis)</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="derma rheumatic"><b>Skin Rash:</b> Any scaly, red
                patches on your scalp, elbows, knees, or belly button?</li>
              <li class="derma rheumatic"><b>Nail Changes:</b> Any pitting (tiny
                dents), lifting of the nail off the bed (onycholysis), or
                thickening?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class=" rheumatic">OTHER RHEUMATOLOGICAL SYMPTOMS
            <ul>
              <li class="rheumatic">Tendon Pain (especially heel pain -
                enthesitis)?</li>
              <li class="rheumatic">Inflammatory-type back pain?</li>
              <li class="ophthalmology rheumatic">Red or painful eyes (uveitis)?</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class=" General">SYSTEMIC SYMPTOMS
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious">Fever, chills, feeling unwell -&gt; Septic
                Arthritis</li>
              <li class="General">Fatigue, weight loss</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- P: Progression -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>:
          Progression</span> <span class="verbal">"Has the swelling been
          getting worse or spreading to other joints?"</span> </li>
      <!-- P: Pattern -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern</span>
        <span class="verbal">"Does it seem to come and go in flares, or is it
          always present?"</span> </li>
      <!-- E: Effect on life -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect
          on Life</span> <span class="verbal">"How has this affected your
          hands? Do you have difficulty with tasks like doing up buttons,
          writing, or gripping things?"</span>
        <ul>
          <li>Impact on fine motor skills</li>
          <li>Difficulty with hobbies or work</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- R: Red Flags -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red
          Flags</span> <span class="verbal">"I just need to ask some specific
          questions to make sure we're not missing anything serious."</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="infectious emergency"><b>A single, hot, red, swollen, and
              exquisitely painful joint</b> (Septic Arthritis until proven
            otherwise).</li>
          <li class="rheumatic">Rapidly progressive swelling affecting multiple
            joints.</li>
          <li class="General">Associated systemic symptoms like high fever or
            unexplained weight loss.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <!-- S: Scale -->
      <li class="point"> <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity
          / Scale</span> <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 1 to 10, how much
          does the pain, stiffness, or swelling bother you?"</span> </li>
    </div>
